## Persist active tab across entity/relationship selections

### Context
In the Ontology Designer (and in the Entities / Relationships detail panels), the
right-hand pane has multiple tabs (Details, Attributes, Actions, Constraints for
entities; Details, Constraints for relationships).  Previously the panel always
reset to the "Details" tab whenever the user clicked a different entity or
relationship, forcing the user to manually re-select their preferred tab each time.

### Changes
1. `src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-shared-panels.js`
   - Added two module-level variables `_entityPanelActiveTab` and `_relPanelActiveTab`
     (default `'details'`) to remember the last active tab per panel type.
   - Updated `switchFormTab()` to write the chosen tab name into the correct
     variable based on the parent form ID (`sharedEntityForm` or
     `sharedRelationshipForm`).
   - Updated the entity form HTML template (inside `renderEntityForm`) to
     substitute the saved tab into `active` classes for both nav links and pane
     `div`s (Details, Attributes, Actions, Constraints).
   - Updated the relationship form HTML template (inside `renderRelationshipForm`)
     in the same way (Details, Constraints), with a safety guard that falls back
     to `'details'` if the stored value is not a valid relationship tab.

### Modified files
- `src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-shared-panels.js`

