## FHIR version selection (R4, R4B, R5)

### Context
The FHIR importer was hard-coded to R5. Users may need R4 (widely deployed) or R4B
for specific healthcare integrations. This change adds a version dropdown to the
FHIR import UI and wires it through the full stack.

### Changes
1. `src/back/core/industry/fhir/FhirImportService.py`
   - Added `FHIR_VERSIONS` class dict mapping version keys (`R4`, `R4B`, `R5`) to
     their HL7 publication base URLs and display labels.
   - Added `DEFAULT_VERSION = "R5"` constant.
   - Added `get_fhir_versions()` static method returning `[{key, label, default}]`.
   - Updated `_fetch_fhir_ttl(version)` to look up the base URL from `FHIR_VERSIONS`
     and raise `ValidationError` for unknown versions. All log/error messages now
     include the version string.
   - Updated `_transform_fhir_to_ontobricks(graph, domain_keys, version)` to embed
     the version in `ontology_info.name`, `ontology_info.description`, and
     `ontology_info.version`.
   - Updated `fetch_and_parse_fhir(domain_keys, version)` to validate, normalise
     (`upper()`), and thread the version through all internal calls.

2. `src/back/core/industry/fhir/__init__.py`
   - Exported `get_fhir_versions`.

3. `src/back/objects/ontology/Ontology.py`
   - `import_industry_ontology(kind, domain_keys, version=None)` — added optional
     `version` param; for FHIR it resolves to `DEFAULT_VERSION` when omitted and
     passes it to `fetch_and_parse_fhir`. The `ont_name` and `desc_prefix` are now
     dynamic (use the actual imported version, not hard-coded "R5").

4. `src/api/routers/internal/ontology.py`
   - Imported `get_fhir_versions`.
   - Added `GET /ontology/fhir-versions` endpoint returning supported versions.
   - Updated `POST /ontology/import-{kind}` to read optional `"version"` from the
     request body and pass it to `import_industry_ontology`.

5. `src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_ontology_import.html`
   - Replaced hardcoded "R5" references with generic "FHIR" text.
   - Added a `<select id="fhirVersionSelect">` dropdown with R4, R4B, R5 (default)
     above the domain checkboxes.

6. `src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-import.js`
   - Reads `fhirVersionSelect` value before the import, falls back to `"R5"`.
   - Includes `version` in the POST body alongside `domains`.
   - Updates the status text and success notification to include the chosen version.

### Modified files
- `src/back/core/industry/fhir/FhirImportService.py`
- `src/back/core/industry/fhir/__init__.py`
- `src/back/objects/ontology/Ontology.py`
- `src/api/routers/internal/ontology.py`
- `src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_ontology_import.html`
- `src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-import.js`

