## Replace native confirm() with custom popup in all import handlers

### Context
All four industry-ontology import handlers (FIBO, CDISC, FHIR, IOF) were using
the browser's native `confirm()` dialog when the user clicked Import with only the
mandatory base domain selected.  Native `confirm()` is blocked in Databricks Apps
and is inconsistent with the rest of the application which uses `showConfirmDialog`.

### Changes
1. `src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-import.js`
   - Replaced `confirm(...)` → `await showConfirmDialog({...})` in the FIBO handler
     (FND only guard).
   - Replaced `confirm(...)` → `await showConfirmDialog({...})` in the CDISC handler
     (Schemas only guard).
   - Replaced `confirm(...)` → `await showConfirmDialog({...})` in the FHIR handler
     (Foundation only guard).
   - Replaced `confirm(...)` → `await showConfirmDialog({...})` in the IOF handler
     (Core only guard).
   All dialogs use the `info-circle` icon, a descriptive title, HTML-formatted body,
   and a labelled confirm button matching the specific importer context.

### Modified files
- `src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-import.js`

