## Fix dependency security vulnerabilities (urllib3, gitpython, idna, strawberry-graphql)

### Context
Five Dependabot alerts were filed against `uv.lock`. Two were already covered by
existing `[tool.uv] constraint-dependencies` entries; this change closes the
remaining three by adding an `idna>=3.13` constraint and bumping the
`strawberry-graphql` floor. Alerts closed:
- urllib3 GHSA-mf9v-mfxr-j63j (decompression-bomb bypass) — was already pinned ✓
- urllib3 GHSA-qccp-gfcp-xxvc (sensitive headers in redirects) — was already pinned ✓
- GitPython GHSA (newline injection / RCE via core.hooksPath bypass) — was already pinned ✓
- idna GHSA-65pc-fj4g-8rjx (bypass of CVE-2024-3651 fix) — fixed here
- strawberry-graphql (GraphiQL exposes HTTP headers in URL) — fixed here

### Changes

1. `pyproject.toml`
   - Bumped `strawberry-graphql[fastapi]` floor from `>=0.312.3` to `>=0.315.4`
     (first release with the GraphiQL headers-in-URL fix).
   - Added `idna>=3.13` to `[tool.uv] constraint-dependencies`
     (3.13 closes the quadratic-time bypass of the CVE-2024-3651 mitigation).

2. `uv.lock`
   - Resolved `idna` 3.11 → 3.15.
   - Resolved `strawberry-graphql` 0.314.3 → 0.315.4.

### Modified files
- `pyproject.toml`
- `uv.lock`

### Tests
`uv run pytest -q` → 2237 passed, 0 failed in 343.78s.

