## Docs: architecture diagrams added to deployment.md

### Context
The deployment guide lacked visual representations of the OntoBricks components,
Lakebase schema layout, data flows, ports, and permission layers.

### Changes
1. `docs/deployment.md` — added new `## Architecture` section (before §1) with five diagrams:
   - **A. Component Architecture** — full topology: two Databricks Apps, bound resources,
     Model Serving, MLflow, MCP↔main REST, external users/Playground
   - **B. Lakebase as Graph DB — Schema Layout** — the three Postgres schemas
     (ontobricks_registry, ontobricks_graph, ontobricks sync), their tables, who creates
     them, and when to run the bootstrap grants
   - **C. Digital Twin Build — Data Flow** — source tables → SQL Warehouse → R2RML →
     Delta VIEW → Lakebase _sync / __app tables → UNION VIEW → SPARQL
   - **D. Network Ports** — local dev vs Databricks Apps, including Lakebase TLS / OAuth
   - **E. Permission Layers** — all four layers (App-level, Unity Catalog, Lakebase
     Postgres, in-app roles) with exact grants and the make target that applies each

### Modified files
- `docs/deployment.md`

### Tests
No code change — documentation only.
